@page "/projects/p2"

<div class="container vw-100">
    <div class="mb-3">
        <NavLink class="btn btn-content" href="/projects" Match="NavLinkMatch.All">Go back to projects</NavLink>
    </div>

    <p><h3>Closed questions database - <span class="orange font-italic">Repeat</span></h3></p>

    <div class="my-2">
        <h3>What?</h3>
        <span>
            This is <b>my first project</b> in ASP.NET and I know that it is far from perfect. This project is more academic than practical, real-world application. 
            <b>Repeat</b> allow to create tests containing multi-choice questions and share them for other users. An user can take a test and see it's summary with test result.
        </span>
    </div>

    <div class="my-2">
        <h3>Why?</h3>
        <span>
            <i>Repetitio est mater studiorum</i>, somebody said. I learn a lot and I am aware that repetition is very important part of learning process.
        </span>
    </div>

    <div class="my-2">
        <h3>How?</h3>
        <span>
            This project aims Domain-Driven Design pattern. 
            It is also full of CRUD operations. 
            Site is based on Razor Pages and MSSQL database. 
            I have used Entity Framework Core as an ORM system.
        </span>
    </div>

    <div class="my-2">
        <h3>Pictures</h3>
        <PhotoGallery Images="Images" />
    </div>

    <div class="my-2">
        <h3>Resources</h3>
        <NavLink class="btn btn-content" href="https://repeat.hubertgad.net/">Visit Repeat</NavLink>
        <button class="btn btn-content">GitHub Repository</button>
    </div>
</div>

@code {
    public List<string> Images { get; set; } = new List<string>
    { "/images/pika.png", "/images/pika.png", "/images/pika.png", "/images/pika.png", "/images/pika.png" };
}